 :tx/rationale "ASSESSMENT FINDING: Coverage Validation Bug in bilateral.rs — compute_depth_weighted_coverage() counts :impl/implements refs as coverage even if the referenced spec entity has been retracted or does not appear in the LIVE projection. Only checks entity count, not :spec/element-type membership. An :impl/implements reference to a deleted or retracted spec still registers as covered if the entity exists anywhere in the store. This inflates F(S)'s C component (weight 0.18), masking the true spec-impl gap. Fix: intersect :impl/implements targets with live spec projection (as forward_scan() already does) before counting coverage. Estimated < 50 lines. VERIFICATION: Create a spec entity, add impl link, retract the spec, verify coverage no longer counts that link. Before fix: coverage inflated. After fix: coverage accurate. Measure F(S) before and after — C component should drop slightly, giving a more honest baseline. INTERACTS WITH: F(S) stagnation (inflated C masks true gap), saw-tooth validation (can't validate model if measurement is wrong), verification sprint (need accurate baseline before sprint). TRACES TO: C6 (falsifiability — the measurement itself must be falsifiable), INV-BILATERAL-002 (coverage accuracy)."
